[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426545&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426545&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

It seems to me that port 20 for FTP is a default; implementations can
agree to use any other port for the data connection (and often do.) But
port 21 is the contact port, and this port number is not negotiable;
when I think of contacting an FTP server, I think of contacting port 21.

I can envision software (in fact, we've been trying to design some)
that does all service lookup by name; a modification of the 4.2 library
routines that look up services by name in a file to use the domain
server would be wonderful. But then my FTP server would need to find
port 21 when looking up TCP/FTP, or it wouldn't be listening at the
right place.

Consider this a vote for change.

Cheers,
chris
